			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">recently a change was made to enable -fPIE on x86-64 linux to ensure that we turn on address space layout randomization for the standalone executables that we generate.

the use of -fPIE overrode -fPIC, so that we are generating code using the local exec rather than general dynamic model.  -fPIE is not appropriate when building shared libraries that are being built with the -fPIC flag.

currently, the shared library targets being built by scons cannot use thread-local storage because of this.  a failure will occur when the .os files are put together into the .so</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-03-13T21:01:42.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-08-19T22:41:49.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
